article.headline: W. Michigan 72, Miami (Ohio) 68
article.story: OXFORD, Ohio -- Shayne Whittington scored 13 points and Western Michigan won its fifth consecutive game, defeating Miami (Ohio) 72-68 Wednesday night. The Broncos (13-7, 5-2 Mid-American Conference) overcame 23 turnovers by shooting 60 percent (12 of 20) in the second half to the RedHawks' 28.6 percent (8 of 28). Miami (7-12, 2-5), which lost its fourth straight, led 35-32 at halftime, but the Broncos started the second half with a 14-5 run. They led 54-45 after David Brown's steal and three-point play with 9:20 left. The RedHawks rallied to lead 63-62 with 4:07 remaining, but Darius Paul's layup and another steal and three-point play by Brown put Western Michigan ahead to stay. Reggie Johnson missed a jumper that could have given Miami a tie with 0:13 left. Paul scored 12 points and Nate Hutcheson and Brandon Pokley had 11 each for the Broncos. Will Felder's 17 points and 13 rebounds led Miami.
